# Language And Localization

- Write all code comments in English, including inline comments, block comments, JSDoc/TSDoc, TODOs, and explanatory notes in source files.
- Do not add Portuguese comments to the codebase. If you touch an existing Portuguese comment, translate it to English when it is directly related to your edit.
- Keep user-facing page text in Brazilian Portuguese because the target audience is in Brazil.
- Treat labels, headings, buttons, form helper text, validation messages, marketing copy, blog content, metadata titles/descriptions, and empty/error states as user-facing text.
- Do not translate Brazilian Portuguese UI or content copy into English unless the user explicitly asks for an English-facing experience.

```tsx
// Good: explain implementation details in English.
const formatter = new Intl.NumberFormat("pt-BR", {
  style: "currency",
  currency: "BRL",
})

export function CheckoutButton() {
  return <button>Finalizar compra</button>
}
```
